 solve the Ni problem, by continuous\ninjection of $^{56}$Ni by the neutrino-driven wind. We suggest that the total\namount of synthesized $^{56}$Ni can be estimated robustly if simulations are\nfollowed up to $\\sim 2$ seconds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Oct 2020 11:40:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 16 Dec 2020 06:04:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-11"}
